results.title: NASA's Perseverance Captures Dust-Filled Martian Whirlwind
results.summary: The six-wheeled geologist spotted the twister as part of an atmospheric exploration of Jezero Crater.

results.title: China to attempt lunar far side sample return in 2024
results.summary: China will launch its Chang’e-6 lunar sample return mission next year in an attempt at a first-ever collection of material from the far side of the moon.

results.title: NASA delays Psyche launch a week
results.summary: NASA has postponed the launch of the asteroid mission Psyche a week to update the configuration of thrusters on the spacecraft.

results.title: SpaceX to close out third quarter with record-breaking Starlink mission
results.summary: SpaceX is set to close the third quarter of 2023 with its 70th launch of the year. The mission, Starlink Group 6-19, is set to lift off this Friday, Sept. 29, at 6:39 PM EDT (22:29 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40), at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

results.title: FAA closes New Shepard mishap investigation
results.summary: The Federal Aviation Administration announced Sept. 26 it had closed the mishap investigation into a failed launch by Blue Origin’s New Shepard vehicle more than a year ago, but said the vehicle is not yet cleared to resume flights.

results.title: FAA closes investigation into Blue Origin rocket failure, requires 21 ‘corrective actions’
results.summary: The Federal Aviation Administration closed its investigation into last year’s failed flight of a cargo mission by Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin, the regulator announced on Wednesday.

results.title: Record-Setting NASA Astronaut, Crewmates Return from Space Mission
results.summary: During his record-breaking mission, Rubio spent many hours on scientific activities aboard the space station, conducting a variety of tasks ranging from plant research to physical sciences studies.

results.title: Frank Rubio Back on Terra Firma After Record-Setting 371-Day Spaceflight
results.summary: NASA astronaut Frank Rubio and two Russian colleagues landed in Kazakhstan this morning after 371 days in space, a new record for a U.S. astronaut. The duration was a surprise. […]

results.title: Soyuz returns ISS crew after record-setting stay
results.summary: A Soyuz capsule landed in Kazakhstan Sept. 27, returning two Russians and one American from the International Space Station after more than a year in orbit.

results.title: After setting new record for responsive launch, Space Force eyes next challenge
results.summary: The U.S. Space Force Victus Nox mission that Firefly Aerospace launched Sept. 14 set a new record for how quickly a national security payload can be put on orbit
